#### Getting Started

First load the seed file, if you haven't yet.

``` html
<script src="<%= @getCdnSeed() %>"></script>
```

Then initialize AlloyUI and load the Carousel module.

``` javascript
AUI().use(
  'aui-panel',
  function(A) {
    // code goes here
  }
);
```

---

#### Using Panel

Create a `div` to contain your panel:

``` html
<div id="myPanel" class="panel">
```

Now create a new instance of Panel component,  set if the panel is collapsible and the `bodyContent` to your desired text. Tell `headerContent` what the header will be. Finally, let's render it!

``` javascript
AUI().ready(
  'aui-panel',
  function(A) {
    new A.Panel(
      {
        bodyContent: "This is my first panel! I can put any information I want here",
        collapsible: true,
        headerContent: 'My First Panel!'
      }
    ).render('#myPanel');
  }
);
```

<div class="alert alert-info">
  <strong>Note:</strong> you could also use `collapsed`, in addtion to `collapsible`. If it is set to `true` the panel will display collapsed.
</div>

