#### Configuring Panel

There are some other options that you can pass to your Panel instance.

For example, you can create a nested panel by  that will appear by defining render to `.panelContainer.bodyNode`.

``` javascript
AUI().ready(
  'aui-panel',
  function(A) {
    new A.Panel(
      {
        bodyContent: "This is my first panel! I can put any information I want here",
        collapsible: true,
        headerContent: 'My First Panel!'
      }
    ).render(panelContainer.bodyNode);
  }
);
```

Also, you can set `boundingBox` to the panel HTML element, set the `contentBox` to where the content will be located in the panel. This allows you to create a panel from the markup in the HTML!

``` javascript
AUI().ready(
  'aui-panel',
  function(A) {
    new A.Panel(
      {
        collapsible: true,
        boundingBox: '#myId',
        contentBox: '#myId > .aui-panel-content'
      }
    ).render();
  }
);
```

